<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-12T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5551: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-12T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 12,
                                        1928—11 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>92. Your telegram No. 173, April 11 [<hi rend="italic">10</hi>], 5 p.m.
                            The Department does not feel that you should make any representations or
                            comment in any way on the action of President Diaz. We prefer not to
                            have anything to do with the candidates, platforms, or issues in this
                            campaign.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>